'''布兰登山'''（Brandon Hill）<ref>{{cite book | last =Weare | first =George Edward | title =Cabot's Discovery of North America | date =July 2009 | publisher =BiblioBazaar | isbn =9781110720804 | url =https://books.google.com/books?id=LB7GnHg1-3MC&q=%22st+brandon+hill%22&pg=PP12 | accessdate =2010-04-15 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title =St Brandon's House | publisher =WindowOnWales | url =http://www.windowonwales.co.uk/rombourne/stbrandons-cabot.html | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20040513034335/http://www.windowonwales.co.uk/rombourne/stbrandons-cabot.html |archive-date =2004-05-13 | accessdate =2010-04-15 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title =Clevedon Hall – a glimpse into its past | publisher =Clevedon Hall Estate | date =2010 | url =http://www.clevedonhall.co.uk/clevedon-hall | accessdate =2010-04-15 |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20100412064847/http://www.clevedonhall.co.uk/clevedon-hall | archivedate =2010-04-12 }}</ref>是一座小山，靠近[[英格兰|英格兰]]西南[[布里斯托尔|布里斯托尔]]市中心, 位于克利夫顿和霍特韦尔斯两区之间。

[[卡博特塔|卡博特塔]]位于山顶，建1897年，以纪念[[约翰·卡博特|约翰·卡博特]]于1497年从布里斯托尔航行到[[纽芬兰岛|纽芬兰岛]]400周年。

山的上部是一个陡峭的公园，一个占地两公顷的自然保护区，开阔的野花草甸。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avonwildlifetrust.org.uk/level1/reserves/brandon_hill.htm|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20051109165418/http://www.avonwildlifetrust.org.uk/level1/reserves/brandon_hill.htm|archivedate=2005-11-09|title=Brandon Hill|work=Reserves|publisher=Avon Wildlife Trust|accessdate=2008-06-04}}</ref>。

山坡的下部在18和19世纪开发。[[圣乔治堂_(布兰登山))|圣乔治堂]]（St George's Church）位于东坡的大乔治街，[[伯克利广场_(布里斯托尔)|伯克利广场]]（Berkeley Square）位于北边，而伊丽莎白女王医院的校舍位于西侧。

== 历史 ==
1174年，格洛斯特伯爵将布兰登山送给议会，用于放牧，1625年成为公共开放空间，可能是英国最古老的市政开放空间。在宗教改革之前，在山顶上矗立着一座供奉爱尔兰圣人布兰（Brendan）的隐修院和小堂。这里居住过许多隐修者，包括修女路济亚。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Clay |first1=Rotha Mary |title=The Hermits and Anchorites of England |url=https://archive.org/details/hermitsanchorite00clay_0 |date=1914 |publisher=Methuen |location=London |page=[https://archive.org/details/hermitsanchorite00clay_0/page/92 92]}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Cottle |first1=Basil |title=The Cult of Saints in Mediaeval Bristol |journal=Avon Past |date=Autumn 1981 |volume=5 |page=8}}</ref> 在18世纪末和19世纪初，这是一个受[[宪章运动|宪章运动]]等改革团体欢迎的公众会议场所，<ref name=council-history>{{cite web |url=http://www.bristol.gov.uk/sites/default/files/documents/leisure_and_culture/parks_and_open_spaces/History%20of%20Brandon%20Hill%20and%20Cabot%20Tower_0.pdf |title=History and architecture of Brandon Hill and Cabot Tower |publisher=Bristol City Council |accessdate=20 August 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121110230607/http://www.bristol.gov.uk/sites/default/files/documents/leisure_and_culture/parks_and_open_spaces/History%20of%20Brandon%20Hill%20and%20Cabot%20Tower_0.pdf |archivedate=10 November 2012 }}</ref> 1832年，这座小山是大改革晚宴的地点。<ref>{{cite web | title =Some Thoughts And Observations On Bristol Radical History Group's Summer Party | work =Archives | publisher =Bristol Radical History Group | date =23 September 2007 | url =http://www.brh.org.uk/articles/brandonhill.html | accessdate =2010-04-15 | archive-date =2011-07-27 | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20110727000441/http://www.brh.org.uk/articles/brandonhill.html | dead-url =no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news | last =Poole | first =Steve | title =Picture in Focus: W. J. Muller and T. L. S. Rowbotham, The Grand Reform Dinner on Brandon Hill (lithograph, 1832) | newspaper =Regional Historian, Issue 7 | publisher =Regional Historian | date =Summer 2001 | url =http://humanities.uwe.ac.uk/regionhistory/rhcnew/RHCarticles/RHC7Poole.doc | accessdate =2010-04-15 |archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20110607000202/http://humanities.uwe.ac.uk/regionhistory/rhcnew/RHCarticles/RHC7Poole.doc | archivedate =2011-06-07 }}</ref>

1843年7月7日，30，000名群众从山上观看[[大不列颠号蒸汽船|大不列颠号蒸汽船]]下水<ref name=council-history/>。1880年1月，20，000名失业工人聚集在山顶，抗议他们的处境，<ref>{{cite book|last1=Richardson|first1=Mike|title=The Bristol Strike Wave of 1889-1890|date=2012|publisher=Bristol Radical History Group|page=6}}</ref>。

